   "source": [
    "In Storytelling With Data, on page 1: examine the pie chart graph in the upper left corner of the graphs.  Please write a short explanation of the pros and cons of this graph.  What do you think of the choice of pie chart as a format?  The color scheme?  The legend?  The title?  How would you draw it differently if you were creating this graph?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "86ab106c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#Pros\n",
    "The pie chart provides a quick visual representation of the survey responses and makes it easy to identify that \"OK\" (40%) is the largest category.\n",
    "Using different colors helps distinguish the categories at a glance.\n",
    "Pie charts are useful for showing how each category contributes to the whole.\n",
    "\n",
    "#Cons\n",
    "Pie charts make it difficult to accurately compare categories with similar percentages, such as \"Excellent\" (12%) and \"Bored\" (11%).\n",
    "The legend requires readers to look back and forth between the chart and the labels instead of displaying the labels directly on the slices.\n",
    "If the title is generic, it does not communicate the key takeaway from the data.\n",
    "\n",
    "$How I Would Improve the Graph\n",
    "\n",
    "If I were creating this graph, I would replace the pie chart with a sorted horizontal bar chart because it makes comparing percentages much easier. If a pie chart had to be used, I would label each slice directly with its category and percentage, choose more distinct colors, and use a title that highlights the main finding, such as \"Most Participants Rated the Experience as OK or Better.\""
   ]
